    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cores of buildings, the parts placed directly underneath the main part of the roof; usually an odd number of bays wide and 2 bays deep. Sometimes used to refer specifically to the central part of a Buddhist temple.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
